commText: de Kock and Rahul are at the crease. de Kock is on strike. Boult will open the attack

Boult to de Kock, FOUR, edged and four, hint of awayswing from Boult - drags de Kock into the drive and finds the edge, two slips in place, but this flies ov er the vacant third slip region, runs away to the ropes

Boult to de Kock, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for de Kock - a genuine half-volley on the pads as Boult went for the inswinger, onto the pads and it's expertly flicked through mid-wicket for a boundary

Boult has this happy knack of getting wickets in the 1st over and he strikes once again - short of a good length and a hint of seam around off, de Kock was looking to work it with the angle through the on-side, but the ball straightens, beats him on the angle and then crashes into the off-stump. The zing bails light up and the Super Giants have lost de Kock early. de Kock b Boult 8(3) [4s-2]

Sandeep Sharma to Stoinis, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

The centurion of the last game has been dismissed for a duck - this is a lovely nut from Sandeep, the wobble seam delivery, pitched up and swung back into the right-hander, Stoinis was lured into the expansive drive, massive gap between bat and ball, the ball crashes through the gate and sends the middle-stump on the floor. Boult to Rahul, FOUR, lovely, the big inswinger from Boult, hoops back into the right-hander - Rahul has the swing covered, closes the face of the bat and then plays the on-drive, beating Chahal's dive at mid-on
Boult to Rahul, no run, on a good length and just outside off, pushed to the off-side
Boult to Rahul, 1 run, tad fuller and on off, dropped in front of mid-off for a quick single

Trent Boult in the first over in IPL 2024 Overs: 9 Runs conceded: 40 Wickets: 5 ER: 4.44 Dots: 36

Avesh Khan to Hooda, no run, back of a length and well wide of off, Hooda went hard on the cut and mistimed it to backward point
Avesh Khan to Hooda, 1 run, Avesh shortens the length on off, Hooda pushes forward and skews a thick inside edge, to the left of mid-on for a single
Avesh Khan to Rahul, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, Rahul leans into the drive, plays witha n open face and can't beat cover-point to his right

Avesh Khan to Hooda, 3 runs, nicely played, short of a good length and just outside off - Hooda rides the bounce and then punches it into the gap wide of cover, long chase for the fielder and he's back for the third
Avesh Khan to Rahul, no run, loose from Rahul, short of a good length and holding its line outside off - too close to cut, Rahul wafts and is beaten on the inside edge
Ravichandran Ashwin, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Ashwin to Hooda, 1 run, tossed up on middle, worked down to long-on for a single
Ashwin to Rahul, no run, a leading edge, and the ball bounces short of backward point - Rahul was looking to work it onto the on-side and closed the bat-face early

Sandeep Sharma to Rahul, no run, that was so close, Rahul would've loooked silly had he been bowled here -shuffled right across on the slog-sweep, Sandeep kept it full and just outside off, past Rahul's left leg and missed the off-stump by a whisker

Sandeep Sharma to Rahul, FOUR, gorgeous, he looks so good when he plays normal cricketing shots - a half-volley from Sandeep, Rahul leans forward, head on top of the ball and then crunches the drive through extra-cover, not one fielder moved

They've taken the strategic break after that expensive 8th over from Avesh. RR started well, but Rahul was composaed, took his time and he's opening up now. Can he get his team to a good score?

21:16 Local Time, 15:46 GMT, 21:16 IST: First time it what feels like ages that a team has been restricted for less than 200. Batting first, the hosts were pegged back by early swing as de Kock and Stoinis were castled in the first couple of overs. With those early wickets, KL Rahul was a bit tepid in the powerplay but broke free after the powerplay, plundering 21 runs off an Avesh Khan over. Hooda from the other end also played some eye catching strokes, carrying on from where he left off against CSK. Both batters scored fifties but Hooda holed out against Ashwin. Rahul however kept scoring some classical strokes, and made use of the longer boundaries to score plenty of doubles. He was looking good for a hundred, but striked out against Avesh Khan at the death. LSG got cameos from Pooran and Badoni at the end, but RR fought back well, conceding just 24 off the last three overs thanks to some solid bowling from Sandeep Sharma. Back shortly for what should be an interesting, dew indifferent chase...

Deepak Hooda - I just bettered what I was doing the last year, took my domestic form into the IPL. The wicket demanded it (on his off-side shots), one side was longer, one side was short. I never thought that it would be my day. I think this is a par score, the wicket is good, we'll have to use the longer side and use our variations., You can't slog blindly, have to be smart and it's a challenge for the bowlers as well. The confidence is high and we're hoping for the best.
